column3: sacrifices and satisfying wishes took places in temples in those days. temples were built under the supervision of the pandian king, ministers and officers. caste wars did not exist in those days. in the 17th century caste wars came into existence. kings, ministers and officers celebrated their birthdays in temples as functions. land was allocated for this. devaram and thiruvayum were recited on those days. arts, music, theatre and folk dance events took place. brick temples, bronze statues and stone figures were installed and ornaments were donated. temples existed as places of storing wealth and material things in addition to serving as places of worship. temple wealth was distributed as loan to common people.  free food was given daily in temples. libraries were built within temples. temple rituals were performed by the village authorities and officers. functions of temples and charities were monitored. punishment was served for errors. stone inscriptions in temples served as historical evidence. renovation of temples involved removing stone inscriptions and reinstalling them.
